{
  "id": 5106043975761920,
  "name": "Web app scope system accent color",
  "summary": "Restricts access to the system accent color for CSS keywords and `accent-color: auto` to be only within a web app and initial profile context.\n\nAccentColor and AccentColorText CSS keywords, pose a significant fingerprinting vector when exposing the user's system colors widely on the web. As such, they're only available in installed web app contexts. Form controls with `accent-color: auto` also match this scope with this feature launch. This introduces more consistent developer and user expectations for system colors and aligns with fingerprinting restrictions for AccentColor[Text].",
